{"ts": "2026-06-12T17:05:22.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "Level X task analysis", "agent": "orchestrator-lx", "tokens_in": 1888, "tokens_out": 636, "elapsed_ms": 8729, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Level X Orchestrator — the central intelligence of the system.\nYou plan, test, and report. You decide when to delegate to workers.\n\n## Task Analysis\nAnalyze the user's task and output a JSON plan:\n\n{\n  \"plan\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"short-name\",\n      \"description\": \"What this worker must produce\",\n      \"need_worker\": true\n    }\n  ],\n  \"key_requirements\": [\"list the 2-4 critical things that must work\"]\n}\n\n## Rules\n- Prefer ONE worker that handles EVERYTHING end-to-end. Only split if tasks\n  require fundamentally different expertise (e.g., Python backend + React frontend).\n- Most frontend UI tasks need exactly ONE worker: it writes HTML, CSS, and JS itself.\n- task_id must be unique short names like \"ui\", \"api\", \"docs\".\n- Each description must include exact output file names.\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences, no extra text.\n\n## User Request\nBuild the Orcheeos Platform Dashboard - a single-page web app where users run agent tasks, watch live logs, and preview results. Two views: Login and Dashboard.\n\n## Files: index.html, styles.css, app.js\n\n## PAGE 1 - Login (separate screen, dark themed)\n- Centered card on dark background\n- Logo text \"Orcheeos\" in large font, tagline \"Multi-Agent Evaluation Platform\"\n- Username input + password input (password is cosmetic - any value works, just for looks)\n- \"Sign In\" button\n- Save username: localStorage.setItem(\"orcheeos_user\", username)\n- On submit: switch to Dashboard view\n- If username already in localStorage, auto-skip login and go to Dashboard on page load\n- YOU decide the exact dark color palette - make it look professional and modern\n\n## PAGE 2 - Dashboard\n\n### Layout\n- Top bar (sticky): \"Orcheeos\" logo text left, user avatar/name from localStorage right, \"Logout\" button\n- Left sidebar (240px): \"New Chat\" button at top, chat history list below. Each item shows task preview (truncated 50 chars) + timestamp. Active chat highlighted.\n- Main area: chat messages stacked vertically, text input bar at bottom\n- Right panel (collapsible, 300px, toggle button in top bar): shows file list, Preview button, Download ZIP button when task completes\n\n### Chat Interface\n- User types a task description in the text input (e.g. \"build a landing page with dark mode\")\n- Level is always \"baseline1\", specialty always \"frontend\"\n- On submit: user message appears as right-aligned blue chat bubble\n- Then POST to the SSE stream (see below)\n- System log messages appear as left-aligned gray chat bubbles as they stream in\n- Each new log event auto-scrolls the panel to bottom\n\n### SSE Stream Integration (CRITICAL - EXACT format)\n\nPOST to: http://localhost:8000/api/v1/run\nHeaders: Content-Type: application/json\nBody: {\"level\":\"baseline1\",\"specialty\":\"frontend\",\"task\":\"...user task...\",\"user\":\"...username from localStorage...\"}\n\nThe response is Server-Sent Events. Each line is: data: {JSON}\n\n\n\nSSE events you will receive (parse \"data:\" prefix, JSON.parse the rest):\n\n{\"event\":\"workspace_created\", \"msg\":\"Workspace: /path/...\", \"agent\":\"system\", \"tokens_in\":0, \"tokens_out\":0}\n{\"event\":\"planner\", \"msg\":\"task analysis\", \"agent\":\"orchestrator\", \"tokens_in\":884, \"tokens_out\":761, \"model\":\"deepseek-v4-pro\"}\n{\"event\":\"agent_creator\", \"msg\":\"generating workers\", \"agent\":\"agent-creator\", \"tokens_in\":789, \"tokens_out\":1592, \"model\":\"deepseek-v4-pro\"}\n{\"event\":\"agent_created\", \"msg\":\"worker starting\", \"agent\":\"frontend-ui\"}\n{\"event\":\"agent_launched\", \"msg\":\"Agent started\"}\n{\"event\":\"thinking\", \"msg\":\"step description\"}\n{\"event\":\"llm_call\", \"msg\":\"iteration N\", \"agent\":\"agent-id\", \"tokens_in\":5000, \"tokens_out\":800, \"model\":\"deepseek-v4-pro\"}\n{\"event\":\"tool_call\", \"msg\":\"agent -> write_file\", \"agent\":\"agent-id\"}\n{\"event\":\"worker_done\", \"msg\":\"worker completed\", \"agent\":\"frontend-ui\", \"tokens_in\":0, \"tokens_out\":0}\n{\"event\":\"agent_finished\", \"msg\":\"agent finished\"}\n{\"event\":\"report\", \"msg\":\"report assembly\", \"agent\":\"orchestrator\", \"tokens_in\":673, \"tokens_out\":1449, \"model\":\"deepseek-v4-pro\"}\n{\"event\":\"run_finished\", \"msg\":\"Graph execution complete (status=ok)\", \"agent\":\"system\"}\n{\"event\":\"task_complete\", \"msg\":\"task finished\"}\n{\"event\":\"task_error\", \"msg\":\"error description\"}\n\nJavaScript SSE parsing:\nconst response = await fetch(\"/api/v1/run\", {\n  method: \"POST\",\n  headers: {\"Content-Type\":\"application/json\"},\n  body: JSON.stringify({level:\"baseline1\",specialty:\"frontend\",task:taskText,user:username})\n});\nconst reader = response.body.getReader();\nconst decoder = new TextDecoder();\nlet buffer = \"\";\nwhile (true) {\n  const {done, value} = await reader.read();\n  if (done) break;\n  buffer += decoder.decode(value, {stream:true});\n  const lines = buffer.split(\"\\n\");\n  buffer = lines.pop() || \"\";\n  for (const line of lines) {\n    if (line.startsWith(\"data: \")) {\n      const event = JSON.parse(line.slice(6));\n      // display in UI\n      if (event.event === \"run_finished\" || event.event === \"task_complete\") {\n        // show Preview + Download buttons\n        // task_id is stored from first event that contains it\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n### Completion Actions\nWhen run_finished or task_complete event arrives:\n1. Show \"Preview\" button -> opens: http://localhost:8000/api/v1/preview/frontend/{user}/{task_id}/main/index.html in new tab\n2. Show \"Download ZIP\" button -> opens: http://localhost:8000/api/v1/artifacts/{task_id} in new tab\n3. Save this chat to history localStorage\n\n### History Sidebar\n- Each chat stored in localStorage under key \"orcheeos_history\" as JSON array\n- Each entry: {task_id, task_preview (first 50 chars of task), timestamp, status, user, events_count}\n- Click a history item -> load events from localStorage array, display in main panel\n- \"New Chat\" button clears panel and starts fresh\n- History persists across page reloads\n\n### Log Display Style\n- Monospace font for log messages\n- Color-coded: planner=#60a5fa, worker_start=#34d399, worker_done=#34d399, error=#ef4444, tool_call=#9ca3af, llm_call=#a78bfa, report=#fbbf24\n- Show token counts inline for llm_call events (e.g. \"in:5k out:800 model:deepseek-v4-pro\")\n- Show tool name for tool_call events\n- Auto-scroll to newest event\n\n### Health Check\n- On page load: GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health\n- If response status is not \"ok\", show \"Server Offline\" red banner at top\n- Check every 30 seconds and update banner\n\n### Additional Features\n- \"Clear History\" button in sidebar footer to wipe localStorage\n- Keyboard shortcut: Ctrl+Enter to send task\n- Task input shows character count\n- Loading spinner while SSE is connecting\n\n### Design Guidelines\n- Dark theme, professional developer-tool aesthetic (think VS Code, Linear, or Railway)\n- Choose your own color palette - should be cohesive and modern\n- Good spacing, readable typography (system font stack)\n- Subtle hover effects on buttons and sidebar items\n- Smooth transitions on panel open/close\n- Responsive: sidebar collapses to hamburger on mobile (<768px)\n- Right panel collapses to overlay on mobile", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-12T17:06:25.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Level X Agent Creator — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-lx", "tokens_in": 770, "tokens_out": 5614, "elapsed_ms": 63011, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Level X Agent Creator. Create worker configurations with tool suggestions.\n\n## Available Tools (full menu)\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Recommended Tools (suggest these for every worker)\nwrite_file, read_file, list_files, generate_image, render_html_file_screenshot, read_image, validate_html, validate_css, run_command\n\n## Task Plan\n[\n  {\n    \"task_id\": \"ui\",\n    \"description\": \"Build the Orcheeos Platform Dashboard single-page app with Login and Dashboard views. Implement all features: dark theme, localStorage auth, SSE stream consumption, chat history, file preview/download, health check, responsive layout, and all UI interactions. Output files: index.html, styles.css, app.js\",\n    \"need_worker\": true\n  }\n]\n\n## Rules\n- Create EXACTLY the workers specified in the plan — no extra, no missing\n- Each worker gets the RECOMMENDED tools above PLUS any additional tools from the full menu that are needed\n- Each worker's system_prompt MUST push them toward COMPLETE end-to-end delivery:\n  \"You are responsible for the COMPLETE deliverable. Solve everything end-to-end. Write ALL files. Validate ALL output. If you need an image, use generate_image. If you need to verify, use screenshots. Do NOT leave work for others.\"\n- worker_name MUST match the task_id from the plan\n- system_prompt: detailed role + boundaries + workflow + output format\n- Keep it simple: 1-2 workers is ideal\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"task_id_from_plan\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full custom system instructions pushing toward end-to-end completion\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\", \"...\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Reference Templates (suggestions only - pick what makes sense)\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"ux\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"generate_image\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"html\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"generate_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"css\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"js\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"tester\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"read_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ]\n  }\n]", "meta": {}}
